The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Greece coach to stay
                                                                                                                                                                                                     EURO DIARY
                      
	Greece coach to stay  
	Salzburg: Greece coach Otto Rehhagel will stay on until 2010 despite the teams disappointing performances, Greek Football Association chief Vassilis Gagatsis said.  
	Euro 2004 winners Greece crashed out even before the final game against Spain on Wednesday. But Gagatsis said Rehhagel, who took over in 2001, would see out his contract, recently extended until 2010.         
	Loew decision         
	 Vienna: Germany coach Joachim Loew wont find out until Wednesday whether he will be banned from the touchline for the following days quarter final match against Portugal.         
	Loew is facing a possible suspension after he and Austria coach Josef Hickersberger were banished to the stands by the referee after they appeared to bicker with the fourth official shortly before halftime on Monday.         
	Portugal at work         
	Neuchatel: After a welcome rest Portugal have begun detailed preparations for Thursdays quarter final while opponents Germany are counting the cost of their belated qualification on Monday. Luiz Felipe Scolaris first-choice players go in after a lot more rest than Germany after securing their berth in the last eight on Wednesday.                                                                                                                            
